  "market_context": "YM daily chart in September 2023 showing a bullish swing from 34799 low to 35045 high. Price retraces back into the OTE zone (0.62–0.79) where a large down-close candle swept lows before displacement higher, leaving behind a bullish order block and an unfilled fair value gap above.",
  "key_observation": "The validated bullish order block's opening price sits outside the OTE zone, so the analyst uses the mean threshold (50% of the order block body) as the refined entry instead of the full opening price.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the bullish swing and draw the 0.62–0.79 OTE Fibonacci retracement between the swing low (34799) and swing high (35045).",
    "Step 2: Note that there is a fair value gap resting above the current price acting as a draw on liquidity for the bullish move.",
    "Step 3: Locate the large down-close candle that swept the lows before price displaced and closed above it, validating it as a bullish order block.",
    "Step 4: Observe that the order block's opening price lies outside the OTE zone, making it suboptimal as an entry.",
    "Step 5: Use the mean threshold (50% of the order block body) as the refined entry point so the entry aligns within the OTE.",
    "Step 6: Anticipate price tagging the mean threshold within the OTE, then expanding higher to fill the fair value gap above."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When an order block's opening price falls outside the OTE zone, use the 50% mean threshold of the order block body as the entry to keep the trade within a discount and reduce stop size while preserving the setup's confluence.",
